{"key":"post-12448379","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12448379</id>\n<content>It appears that several of you guys are misusing the term isolate.&amp;nbsp; An isolate is a single-sector strain with only one set of genetics.&amp;nbsp; You can't get that sucking up a cloud of mycelium in water, partly because you can't see sectoring in water, and also because it takes five or six transfers at least, to get to single sectors. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is why we use the two-dimensional space which is the flat plane of a petri dish.&amp;nbsp; It allows us to see things that in three dimensional space(LC) would be little more than a blob.&amp;nbsp; It also seems the effort and trouble is much more than spending six bucks on a plastic tote and cutting a couple of holes for your arms to stick through.&amp;nbsp; A still air box need not be a glovebox.&amp;nbsp; All you need is a place away from drafts and you can then do agar work with surgical gloves on your hands.&amp;nbsp; It may not succeed 100% of the time, but it's a six dollar alternative to a $500 flowhood.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12448396</next>\n<prev>12448270</prev>\n<first>12443073</first>\n<last>12487434</last>\n<when>1272122370</when>\n<utime>04/24/10 06:19 PM</utime>\n</post>"}